      "writtenOn": "2020-07-24T17:33:21Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Sorry, yes. I was just pointing out that we should be using 512/1023 or 2048/4095. For limited range matrices, that\u0027s fine - we need to change several other values, so having separate matrices makes sense. For full-range, the bit depth ends up changing one value in the entire matrix.\n\nSo, we could offer 10 and 12 bit full-range, if you think that\u0027s important. Otherwise, this uses the 8-bit zero for all the full-range matrices, and the \"correct\" zero for the 10 and 12-bit limited matrices.",
      "parentUuid": "d9aed18f_de9bfd66",
